    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>School of painting that flourished in the mid-16th century in eastern Tibet; it was begun by Jamyang Khyentse Wangchuk (b. 1524). Attention to detail, continued Chinese influence, and a new way of treating the background are hallmarks of this school.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
